post_cb({"bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_34828161_34828179_0": {"length": 5, "quality": 0.7142857142857143, "section_id": 5419}}, "n3337": {"so_34828161_34828179_0": {"length": 5, "quality": 0.7142857142857143, "section_id": 5214}}, "n4659": {"so_34828161_34828179_0": {"length": 6, "quality": 0.8571428571428571, "section_id": 6841}}}, "34828161": {"ViewCount": "1454", "Body": "<p>Can virtual functions like <code>X::f()</code> in the following code</p>\n<pre><code>struct X \n{\n    constexpr virtual int f() const \n    {\n        return 0;\n    }\n};\n</code></pre>\n<p>be <code>constexpr</code>?</p>\n", "AcceptedAnswerId": "34828179", "Title": "Can virtual functions be constexpr?", "CreationDate": "2016-01-16T14:34:02.333", "Id": "34828161", "CommentCount": "4", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastActivityDate": "2016-01-16T14:36:06.747", "Score": "4", "OwnerUserId": "1335865", "Tags": "<c++><c++11><virtual-functions><constexpr>", "AnswerCount": "1"}, "34828179": {"Id": "34828179", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>No. From [dcl.constexpr]/3 (7.1.5, \"The <code>constexpr</code> specifier\"):</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_34828161_34828179_0\">The definition of a <code>constexpr</code> function shall satisfy the following requirements:</p>\n<p id=\"so_34828161_34828179_1\">\u2014 it shall not be virtual</p>\n</blockquote>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2016-01-16T14:36:06.747", "CommentCount": "4", "CreationDate": "2016-01-16T14:36:06.747", "ParentId": "34828161", "Score": "21", "OwnerUserId": "596781"}});